-- Hot Shareholder Drahi Seeks to Sell 20% Stake, Calcalist Reports
-- B y   G w e n   A c k e r m a n
-- 2012-03-26T06:54:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-26/hot-shareholder-drahi-seeks-to-sell-20-stake-calcalist-reports.html
Hot Telecommunication System Ltd. (HOT) ’s
controlling shareholder French businessman Patrick Drahi is in
talks with the U.S. Blackstone Group LP to sell 20 percent of
the company through which he holds Hot, Calcalist said today,
without saying where it got the information.  Drahi’s price for the stake values Hot at 5 billion
shekels, Calcalist said. Hot’s market valuation at market close
yesterday was 3 billion shekels.  Moti Scherf, spokesman for Drahi in  Israel , declined to
comment on the report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Gwen Ackerman in Jerusalem at 
 gackerman@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Louis Meixler at 
 lmeixler@bloomberg.net  